\begin_inset Formula 
\[
\Delta V=\alpha_{1}(T_{c}-T_{e})
\]

\end_inset

which peculiarly enough, depends only on the seeback cofficient of metal
 two.
 This maybe wrong because if it were so simple to find the seeback cofficient
 of one metal in isolation, Ashcroft won't say use a superconductor instead
 of the second metal (a superconductor doesn't exhibit seeback (cofficient
 is zero))
